<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="866" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6342.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Nogales</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A very bitter resentment here and in the State [of Sonora] resulting from
                            the killing of Madero. The State will not submit to the Provisional
                            Government at Mexico City.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowman</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>